last_episode_to_air.name: Runes
last_episode_to_air.overview: Runes are the letters of an ancient Germanic writing system that harkens back to a mythological age filled with heroes, magic, and mystery. To the Nazis, runes were about power, and represented proof of Aryan dominance. Himmler made rune studies obligatory for SS officers as he believed they held mystical power and even placed protective runes on SS uniforms and buildings.

name: Secret Nazi Expeditions
overview: WWII. The Nazis create an elite team of scientists to scour the globe and mount expeditions to extreme and harsh locations. Their mission: rewrite history and collect ancient artifacts in the name of the thousand-year Reich.

episodes.name: The Lost Continent
episodes.overview: Atlantis. The legendary continent that sank to the bottom of the sea. Many have searched for it in vain, but as the Nazis rose to power, Himmler was convinced Atlantis could be found and instigated a series of expeditions to uncover its secrets.

episodes.name: Walking with Witches
episodes.overview: Witchcraft has been practiced for centuries around the world, persevering as sinister forces attempted to wipe it out or warp it into something evil. In Nazi Germany, mysterious questions about witchcraft swirled among SS leaders...

episodes.name: Into the Mountains
episodes.overview: The Himalayas, the world's highest mountain range, are believed to be home to a host of mythical powers and creatures. A pseudoscientific theory embraced by the Nazis claimed their Aryan ancestors sought refuge here during a mythical ice age...

episodes.name: The Quest for the Holy Grail
episodes.overview: The Holy Grail, an ancient relic shrouded in mystique and lore. As the Third Reich rises to power, Himmler and the SS become fixated on the Grail, interpreting much of the myth surrounding it as fact, and the quest for it as attainable...

episodes.name: Cro Magnon
episodes.overview: Over centuries, researchers have come closer to understanding the true origins of humanity, but there are still fundamental questions up for debate. There is power in this debate and it becomes the fixation of a nefarious power as Heinrich Himmler, leader of the Nazi's SS, turns his attention to proving the Paleolithic past of Germany's Aryan race.
